  "prompt": "Which are the 4 stroke bikes in India?",
  "response": "In India, there are numerous 4-stroke motorcycles available from various manufacturers. Here are some examples from popular brands:\n\n### Bajaj\n1. **Pulsar Series** (e.g., Pulsar NS200, Pulsar RS200, Pulsar 150)\n2. **Avenger Series** (e.g., Avenger 220 Cruise, Avenger 160 Street)\n3. **Dominar Series** (e.g., Dominar 400, Dominar 250)\n\n### Hero MotoCorp\n1. **Splendor Series** (e.g., Splendor Plus, Splendor iSmart)\n2. **HF Deluxe**\n3. **Glamour Series** (e.g., Glamour 125, Glamour Xtec)\n4. **Passion Series** (e.g., Passion Pro, Passion XPro)\n5. **Xtreme Series** (e.g., Xtreme 160R, Xpulse 200)\n\n### Honda\n1. **CB Series** (e.g., CB Shine, CB Unicorn, CB Hornet 160R)\n2. **Activa Series** (e.g., Activa 6G, Activa 125)\n3. **Honda Hness CB350**\n4. **Honda CBR Series** (e.g., CBR 250R)\n\n### TVS\n1. **Apache Series** (e.g., Apache RTR 160, Apache RTR 200, Apache RR 310)\n2. **Jupiter**\n3. **Ntorq 125**\n\n### Yamaha\n1. **FZ Series** (e.g., FZ Fi V3, FZS Fi V3)\n2. **YZF R15 V3**\n3. **MT-15**\n4. **Fascino**\n\n### Royal Enfield\n1. **Classic 350**\n2. **Bullet Series** (e.g., Bullet 350)\n3. **Interceptor 650**\n4. **Himalayan**\n\n### KTM\n1. **Duke Series** (e.g., Duke 200, Duke 250, Duke 390)\n2. **RC Series** (e.g., RC 200, RC 390)\n\n### Suzuki\n1. **Gixxer Series** (e.g., Gixxer 155, Gixxer SF)\n2. **Intruder 150**\n3. **Access 125**\n\nThese are just a few examples of 4-stroke bikes available in India. The market is vast and continues to evolve with new models being introduced regularly.",
